race.comment: COMONGIN (7) progressive gelding who looks destined for better things. Bounced off his good first-up second with a gritty on pace head victory over 1100m at Coonamble. Well in again with the claim and gets the gun run. CRESTA RUN (8) sent to town after giving them a galloping lesson when leading throughout over 1200m at Moree. Failed to handle the steep class rise when a tiring tenth over 1000m at Randwick. Kept fresh and shapes as the main danger. REPRISAL (3) much better effort at his second run for the new yard. Look for him doing his best work late. TRUMPTY DUMPTY (6) is racing in good order and is not to be discounted.
